<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="3"><strong><strong>Standing Cable Machine Face Pulls With Dumbbell Shrugs</strong></strong></h3>



<p>The first exercise of this superset involves using a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cable-shoulder-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cable machine</a>. Face pulls target your rear deltoids and upper traps. Dumbbell shrugs target your upper trap muscles and rhomboids —your upper back muscles.&nbsp;</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Cable Machine Face Pulls</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Cable-Machine-Face-Pulls.jpg" alt="Cable Machine Face Pulls" class="wp-image-6460" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Cable-Machine-Face-Pulls.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Cable-Machine-Face-Pulls-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Cable-Machine-Face-Pulls-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Cable-Machine-Face-Pulls-768x430.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cable Machine Face Pulls Guide.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong><strong><strong>How To Do</strong></strong></strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Set the cable machine at face height.</li>



<li>Find the rope attachment and connect it to the cable.</li>



<li>Grab the rope and grasp it with both hands with a narrow grip.</li>



<li>Pull the rope towards your face, keeping your arms parallel to the ground, elbows bent.</li>



<li>With control, slowly return the rope to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tips</strong></h4>



<ul>
<li>Adjust the pulley to the upper chest level and use a rope attachment.</li>



<li>Pull the rope towards your face, elbows high and outwards.</li>



<li>Squeeze your shoulder blades together at the peak of the movement.</li>
</ul>



