<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Standing Dumbbell Bicep Curls</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-image aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Standing-Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls-1.jpg" alt="Standing Dumbbell Bicep Curls" class="wp-image-6533" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Standing-Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls-1.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Standing-Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls-1-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Standing-Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls-1-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Standing-Dumbbell-Bicep-Curls-1-768x430.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Standing Dumbbell Bicep Curls Guide.
<span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"><strong><strong><strong>How To Do</strong></strong></strong></h4>



<ol>
<li>Hold a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing forward. Let the weights hang at your sides.</li>



<li>Curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position at a 180-degree angle.</li>
