<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start"><strong>How To Warm Up For A Shoulder Superset</strong></h2>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-To-Warm-Up-For-A-Shoulder-Superset.jpg" alt="How To Warm Up For A Shoulder Superset" class="wp-image-6560" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-To-Warm-Up-For-A-Shoulder-Superset.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-To-Warm-Up-For-A-Shoulder-Superset-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-To-Warm-Up-For-A-Shoulder-Superset-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/How-To-Warm-Up-For-A-Shoulder-Superset-768x430.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Tips to warm up for a shoulder superset. <span>Photo: Racool_studio/Freepik</span> </figcaption></figure></div>


<p>Warming up is an important part of preparing for any <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/morning-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">exercise routine</a> to prepare the muscles and joints for the upcoming workout. Think of this as <em>waking up</em> your muscles. By doing this, you can promote shoulder mobility.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>Warming up your muscles <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833972/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">increases muscle temperature and blood flow</a> <sup>[6] </sup>to the muscles you train. This contributes to improved exercise performance and can prevent injuries. Experts recommend warm-ups should be around 5-15 minutes in length before starting your workout routine.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It’s important to remember that <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833972/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">cooling down</a> <sup>[6] </sup>after lifting heavy weights is also important to stretch muscles and prevent injury.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Arm Circles</strong></h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-14199" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Arm-Circles-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Arm Circles. <span>Photo: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<ul>
<li>Duration: One minute.</li>



<li>Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and extend your arms to the sides. Begin making small rotations in a circular motion. After 30 seconds, reverse the circles.</li>
</ul>



